	<Title>
		Herbal supplements: Caution ahead
	</Title>
	<Body>
		&lt;p&gt;If you take herbal supplements, include a dose of safety in your routine: 1. Don&apos;t exceed the recommended dosages. 2. Tell your doctor what you&apos;re taking. Some herbs may interfere with other drugs or have other harmful effects. 3. Avoid herbs if you&apos;re pregnant or breast-feeding, unless your doctor approves. 4. Be cautious about using herbal products manufactured in foreign countries.&lt;/p&gt;
